From the basement to The Barclays… 🏀🎤

A lot of times when people ask me “what do you do?” I have a lot of hesitancy answering that question. Not because I don’t believe in myself, but because I’d rather not give energy to the negative or sarcastic tone that “rap” is usually met with. “Haha, what do you really do though?!

Well last Friday, I REALLY performed in front of a packed arena at the Nets game as an independent artist. While the story is far from over, this was the best chapter yet.

Thank you to The @brooklynnets for the opportunity and every single person who sent me a note / tuned into the game. WE did that! Never stop pursuing your passions and trust God’s timing. 🙏🏾🙏🏾
Tell me it’s a fluke, but i went and did it ✌🏽 (swipe for a surprise) 🎶🎵
